items.name: Dondasch
items.addedLore: The sheer bond between Adamastor and Urdar has manifested itself into a physical form due to their duress. Such power is not to be abused...

items.name: Summa
items.addedLore: An auxiliary power core of the powerful TERA-4M Mining robot line. It controls the robots by giving the bearer a compulsion to break new grounds and progress further without heed.

items.name: Durum's Serenity
items.addedLore: Carried by the Durum Protector, this small necklace holds but an ounce of the vibrance and life of the Durum Isles.

items.name: Kahontsi Ohstyen
items.addedLore: Wielded by the chief of the Tromsian jungle's zombie tribes, the augmentable crystals within it focus natural elemental energies to intense levels.

items.name: Helm Splitter
items.addedLore: One of Skien's many deadly weapons. This warhammer, despite the massive weight of the hammerhead, was able to be swung by Skien fast enough to be a blur.

items.name: Blade of Shade
items.addedLore: The fabled weapon of the titular dark Assassin, the blade's small stature hides its true powers. Shadows undulate about the hilt.

items.name: Plague Staff
items.addedLore: Carried by the Olux Plague Doctor, this simple-looking stick subtly oozes with an unidentifiable substance that is invigorating to the holder, and lethally venomous to anything else.

items.name: Deadeye
items.addedLore: The weapon of the fearsome lone bandit, Rymek Luke, it is unique in that it is designed to fire small metal rounds instead of more traditional projectiles.

items.name: Haros' Oar
items.addedLore: The weathered oar of Haros, the outcast ferryman of Charon's Forsaken Legion. Magical implements have been jury-rigged onto the silver pole, glowing dull out of his bony grasp.

items.name: Stave of the Legends
items.addedLore: Crafted exclusively by the Temple of the Legends' mages, this stave is honorary to Mages who best the Temple's Grand Magus.

items.name: Binding Brace
items.addedLore: An oppressively dark aura emanates from this shackle, dampening both the will and magic potency of those that wear it.

items.name: Marius' Prison
items.addedLore: "I know the Beast may return one day...but these chains shall bind it for eternity." The inscription glows bright in the darkness.

items.name: Bonder
items.addedLore: It looks like they spelled the name wrong...

items.name: Braker
items.addedLore: Seems like the name is misspelled a little bit.

items.name: Slider
items.addedLore: The spelling seems to have been botched.

items.name: Stinger
items.addedLore: If it weren't for that stray mark, this would be spelled correctly...

items.name: Adamantite
items.addedLore: Adamantite is a soft metal often added to exotic medicine to increase one's health, but a revolutionary blacksmith on Black Road, created a chestplate with an Adamantite alloy, which is advertised to bolster the users endurance.

items.name: Aersectra
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Alazarin
items.addedLore: This bloody palette knife was used to kill only two people before it was abandoned - a killer who broke into a great artist's home, and the artist who struck the blow.

items.name: Albedo
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Almuj's Walker
items.addedLore: There used to be a constant battle between Almuj's thieves over these feather-light, gold-plated boots, until one day they were stolen by an unknown pickpocket and never seen again.

items.name: Almuj's Daggers
items.addedLore: The reigning king of thieves in Almujs underworld would brandish this golden dagger to his enemies so fast, you wouldnt even realise your wallet was now missing.

items.name: Anarchy
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Anchoryl
items.addedLore: Despite being a much smaller settlement compared to the mighty citadel of Rodoroc, the dwarven smiths of Thanos still can forge mighty products, such as these heavy diamond-alloy boots.

items.name: Ancient Wand
items.addedLore: It is thought that this primitive wand was used by early man to create the first spells. It is made from a wood that no longer exists.

items.name: Andesite Aegis
items.addedLore: Andesite is a stone commonly used for weapons and construction, but tends to be ineffective as armor when impure. This sturdy chestplate, however, is testament to the strength of pure andesite.

items.name: Antimony
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Aquarius
items.addedLore: The symbol of the river is a name that is often synonymous with this garment, with many water like qualities surrounding it, heavily bathed in magical meaning.

items.name: Aries
items.addedLore: Two iron horns adorn this helmet to enhance the warriors of the Eradian, Dwarves who specifically rode Rams into battle at incredible speed.

items.name: Arma Gauntlet
items.addedLore: Stories say that should anyone wield both of these fearsome gauntlets in battle, they will become unkillable in a fight. The second gauntlet, however, has never been found.

items.name: Audacity
items.addedLore: A powerful mental curse surrounds these boots, inciting uncontrollable rage into the wearers, as well as the power to enact it upon others.

items.name: Bad Wolf
items.addedLore: The runic message carved on these enigmatic boots cover hundreds of different languages, many of them disused, but what has been translated seems to describe a disaster soon to arrive to the world.

items.name: Bedruthan
items.addedLore: Stone shorn from mountains by the roiling sea gathered on the shores of Llevigar one day, washed onto the sand in the shape of a massive spear. It was taken as an omen, and the stones were forged into a true weapon.

items.name: Bismuthinite
items.addedLore: An extremely rare metallic ore only found within the island region of Corkus, it is normally used in decorative dyes. However, a mishap one day caused the discovery of strange and cumulative effects when exposed to traditional magicks.

items.name: Black
items.addedLore: Hewn from the great obsidian spires surrounding the massive Nether gate, this fiercely-hooked dagger absorbs light and magic energy alike to create a desolate void wherever it is wielded.

items.name: Blade of Purity
items.addedLore: The creator of this polished white blade insists that its true power will never be unlocked, for only those who are not influenced by the elements of the world know truly how to utilize it.

items.name: Blessed Wrappings
items.addedLore: The thick, Bovemist-sanctified cloth is worn by their priests during certain religious ceremonies. It clears the mind and purifies the body.

items.name: Blossom
items.addedLore: A mystical sapling native to the shores of Mage Island has been fashioned into this simple staff. Even uprooted, you notice its continuous growth.

items.name: Blue Mask
items.addedLore: The Blue Mask's physical traits are equal to that of paper, but the mystical properties enhance the wearers personal skills tenfold. The mask is thought to originate from an ancient Dernel tribe.

items.name: Booster Plate
items.addedLore: A marvel of Corkus' electromagical advancements, this high-tech chestplate is equipped with steam jets to boost the user's speed, at a minimal cost to protection.

items.name: Bough of Fir
items.addedLore: Crafted from Mandragora roots and adorned with decorative wreaths of Elven pines, these wands are utilized in Efilim's solstice festivals to celebrate each passing year of Villager and Elven comradery.

items.name: Bovine Killer
items.addedLore: This helmet was worn long ago by an infamous assassin who plagued Bovemist sites for decades. It was crafted of the still-bloody skin of their most prized and worshiped cows.

items.name: Brass Brand
items.addedLore: Built by Cerid to accrue raw static charge from the surroundings and direct it at opponents, the blade's chief failing is that the wielder is not rendered immune to their own discharge as intended.

items.name: Bridge of the Divide
items.addedLore: These leggings hold the interest of many researching the corruption, as they are the only documented case of a non-corrupt fusion of dark and light energy, made of pure twilight.

items.name: Broken Balance
items.addedLore: Torn scraps of metal line the inside of these boots. They provide no protection, instead forcing a constant adrenaline rush while worn.

items.name: Buster Bracer
items.addedLore: A mighty, earth-shatteringly powerful weapon was destroyed for fear of its raw power, and the pieces buried. They were unearthed decades later, and were reforged into various items including this sturdy bracer.

items.name: Wybel Paw
items.addedLore: Even reduced to just the bones, you can't help but feel bad for the poor thing this paw came from.

items.name: Cage of Bones
items.addedLore: The ancient bones of the demon Garaheth are stronger than steel. They clamp down when worn to constrict the bearer, inciting a slow madness.

items.name: Call of the Void
items.addedLore: Originating from the unspeakable dark land, looking into the helmet will show nothing but darkness. Wearing it is said to reverse your morality, as if it were draining your will to live into the void.

items.name: Call to Concord
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Reverberating with the bravery and residual strength of fallen Wynn soldiers, every casualty only serves to harden the resolve it instills in the wearer.

items.name: Cancer
items.addedLore: 450 years ago a demonic plague like no other spread through Gavel, killing thousands. That is, until a priest encased the disease inside a helmet and warned everyone never to wear it.

items.name: Capricorn
items.addedLore: During a spiritual journey to Kato temple, the sage Capian was presented with powerful spiritual boots with the intention to be used for peaceful magic, and not hard combat.

items.name: Cascade
items.addedLore: A great magical cataclysm at Mage Island brought on by a strange, seemingly disconnected series of events resulted in this wand absorbing nearly uncontrollably high levels of magic.

items.name: Chained Pixels
items.addedLore: Materials of all sorts have been lashed together in this crude, blocky set of leggings. From darksteel to leather to rotting wood, each part is a perfect square. It has, so far, been impossible to recreate.

items.name: Chakram
items.addedLore: Despite appearing as a basic blade when held, strange spiritual magic changes its form into a sharp, ring-like cutting edge when used to attack. Only one person was known to master the weapon's abilities.

items.name: Chaleur
items.addedLore: This blackiron blade was left to sear in the desert for months on end by a fanatical berserker. It burned him alive as he cut down those who opposed him.

items.name: Chimaera
items.addedLore: The one true Chimera in existence is sought by many, for great stories are told of its gifts to the worthy. One such gift was a simple fur coat, which gave the wearer but a taste of its power.

items.name: Clairvoyance
items.addedLore: The powerful psychic energies surrounding this bow are rumored to increase accuracy, though this has not been refuted by any reliable source.

items.name: Clash Hook
items.addedLore: The wear on this humble war pick's blade has only made it more effective in combat, allowing its users to make unexpected parries of opponents' attacks by hooking and hitting through the weapon.

items.name: Cluster
items.addedLore: Perhaps one is weak. To be ignored. Perhaps two are not much better. But what of five? Ten? Twenty?...

items.name: Concentration
items.addedLore: The forger of this ring had to endure 30 long days of smelting various metals only found in the ocean. A single mistake would ruin the creation. The mystic metals are said to seep into the wearers skin to gently replenish their resolve.

items.name: Conductor
items.addedLore: Using an unorthodox method of smithing, these copper leggings are insulated with an extremely conductive blend of liquid to improve electrical discharge.

items.name: Black Catalyst
items.addedLore: Even simply looking at these odd rings gives way to a compulsion to wear two of them, despite all better judgement.

items.name: Crackshot
items.addedLore: This heavy crossbow forces a strange compulsion in its users when wielded. They will often refuse to even shoot unless entirely certain of a hit.

items.name: Crystal
items.addedLore: Forged on Mage Island, the sparkling liquid-like armour is as hard as obsidian, but light and fluid as water. It glistens with the magic of the ocean winds.

items.name: Cyclo
items.addedLore: A centuries-old storm spirit was banished to these tight boots for his destructive actions. His fury empowers those who wear them with the great force of a raging cyclone.

items.name: Ra
items.addedLore: Undecipherable symbols are carved into this long arm band, though the fiery glow and bright jewel has led archaeologists to believe it is somehow related to the sun.

items.name: Witherhead's Bow
items.addedLore: Wielded by the master of the Decrepit Sewers Dungeon, the arrows of this bow causes the target's body to slowly wither away.

items.name: Arakadicus' Body
items.addedLore: Long strips of chitin discarded from the mother of spiders Arakadicus still contain traces of her wicked powers, but few have survived the attempts to harvest them.

items.name: Dark Shroud
items.addedLore: Wearing this deceptively simple shroud causes the user to fade into the shadows, sometimes flickering out of existence for a moment.

items.name: Darkiron Scrap
items.addedLore: Despite being only an impure scrap of the normally sturdy blackiron, these heavy leggings still have extreme defensive capabilities.

items.name: Dead Sands
items.addedLore: Found in the middle of the Almuj desert, these greaves seem to slowly poison all life around them. Theorists suggest they were the handiwork of a wicked necromancer, though the truth is not known.

items.name: Detlas' Legacy
items.addedLore: One of Detlas founding buildings was struck by lightning 60 years ago and burnt to the ground, apart from one wooden beam that began to glow. It was fashioned into an exclusive wand for resident mages.

items.name: Diablo
items.addedLore: One of the most unstable wands known to man, using the bark of the Flerisi trunk it reaps firey destruction upon its enemies.

items.name: Dislocater
items.addedLore: Often, the leader of brute gangs would use this dagger to threaten his followers into making sure they did not fail him.

items.name: Empire Builder
items.addedLore: This golden staff was recovered from deep within the tombs of Almuj. Nothing else was found in the room except the words 'Beware the user with unlimited imagination'.

items.name: Esclavage
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Erratio
items.addedLore: The blind prophet who crafted this macabre breastplate used the bones of only the most ruthless justiciars and executioners. Its wearers are supposedly destined to only die either a heroic or a just death.

items.name: Eruption
items.addedLore: No one expected the WynnExcavation volcanic site to produce any valuable materials, but this heavy, obsidian-blend bow silenced the critics.

items.name: Ethereal
items.addedLore: Supposedly based off of the wand of master mage Ethe, this wand is plated with magic-focusing jewels and heavy gold, yet somehow remains entirely weightless.

items.name: Fenmask
items.addedLore: This matted tangle of vines and marshland plants contains various herbal remedies woven into it. It is oddly comfortable, despite the thorns coating the inside.

items.name: Fierte
items.addedLore: Only the most honourable warriors of Gavel's army are presented the trident shaped spear, forged from the rarest metal from the molten heights.

items.name: Fierce Thunder
items.addedLore: Every time this spear hits an enemy, a sharp electrical jolt hits the users hands that forces powerful lightning to release.

items.name: Fissure
items.addedLore: Dwarven folklore tells of this mighty maul, used by gods to break mountains, shape continents, and crack the earth to form caverns.

items.name: Flameshot Hilt
items.addedLore: Found abandoned in the caves of the Doguns, these odd weapons are designed to shoot jets of sheer flame instead of hitting enemies traditionally. They are in terrible disrepair, and none know how to fix them.

items.name: Follow The Wind
items.addedLore: A lost relic from the Wind Fortress, a mythical stronghold of the Sky Islands that fell into the Void long ago. A small mechanism within the bracelet points towards its place of origin.

items.name: Gale's Force
items.addedLore: Those who have used this near-weightless bow all seem to tell tales of how they see Gale's spirit fighting alongside them.

items.name: Gemini
items.addedLore: The gods of air and thunder, frustrated with being physically insubstantial alone, decided to band together to forge the ultimate leggings of defense.

items.name: Giant's Bracer
items.addedLore: This ill-fitting, bulky chestplate was never intended to be a chestplate at all. Rather, it is a broken fragment of an arm bracer, from the time of giants.

items.name: Giant Step
items.addedLore: Found in a mystically-charged Giant ruin, these snug boots recall fond memories, incite calmness, and provide comfort for the wearer.

items.name: Glacial Crest
items.addedLore: Used for endurance training on the Icy Islands, this bow forces the wielder's body temperature to drop to near-hypothermic levels.

items.name: Glare
items.addedLore: The blazing sun has been revered by many druidic sects as a god in its own right, and the jewel in this brilliant wand glows with the brightness of their holy star.

items.name: Gospel
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Gravity
items.addedLore: No one knows how this extremely dense chestplate can even logically exist. It is almost paradoxical in nature, and affects its wearers in unfathomable ways.

items.name: Greaves of the Veneer
items.addedLore: Forged from mystic, previously unknown metals revealed in the deepest dwarven mining site to date, these sleek, glowing greaves are believed to be utterly indestructible.

items.name: Grillface
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] The old facemasks of the Eradian guards were forged from raw magma, and enchanted to remain searingly hot, so as to brand the wearer eternally with the mark of Rodoroc's elite.

items.name: Anima-Infused Helmet
items.addedLore: Infused with the classical magicks of fire, water, and thunder, this ornately-crafted helmet is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

items.name: Boreal-Patterned Aegis
items.addedLore: Engraved with the beauty and mystery of the boreal lights, this ornately-crafted chestplate is given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

items.name: Contrast
items.addedLore: The runes carved onto the gold beads strung along this simple necklace translate into various words meaning variance. It provides many abilities though unexplainable means.

items.name: Gaea-Hewn Boots
items.addedLore: Forged in direct tribute to the earth and its aspects, these ornately-crafted boots are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

items.name: Infused Hive Bow
items.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this bow has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its string radiates a spectrum of colors.

items.name: Infused Hive Dagger
items.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this dagger has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It leaves afterimages that pulsate in a spectrum of colors.

items.name: Hephaestus-Forged Greaves
items.addedLore: Honoring a mythical dwarven smith lost to the legends, these ornately-crafted greaves are given only to those who have bested the Mistress of the Hive.

items.name: Infused Hive Wand
items.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this wand has been infused with energy from all five known elements. It subtly glows in a spectrum of colors.

items.name: Infused Hive Spear
items.addedLore: Deceptively plain-looking, this spear has been infused with energy from all five known elements. Its tip shimmers in a spectrum of colors.

items.name: Intensity
items.addedLore: The runes carved into this simple gold ring translate into various words meaning power. It amplifies elemental energies in inexplicable ways.

items.name: Prowess
items.addedLore: The runes carved into this simple gold cuff translate into various words meaning mastery. It amplifies the ability of the wearer in mysterious ways.

items.name: Harwrol
items.addedLore: The runes carved onto the spear shift appearance so quickly as to be illegible, but those who wield it supposedly will learn their meaning.

items.name: Heliophilia
items.addedLore: This peculiar shawl is eternally warm to the touch, and shimmers brilliantly in the sunlight. It is rumored to give amazing health benefits and good fortune to those who wear it.

items.name: Hellstrand
items.addedLore: The Order of the Abyss crafted this bow in opposition to the House of Talor's holy relic. Holding it for too long will strain and warp the user's mind.

items.name: Heracul
items.addedLore: Reconstructed from mere wooden scraps of its former self, this extremely heavy crossbow still contains immense power. It was intended for use with a lost suit of armor, of which only one piece remains.

items.name: Hetusol
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] The make of this massive cloak is unlike anything seen before among the provinces. Foreign images shift and melt in ethereal projections within the inside.

items.name: Hexed Amulet
items.addedLore: Although the warlock's curse placed upon this simple, Olux-crafted charm will reduce the abilities of the wearer significantly, its original luck-bolstering properties still are in place.

items.name: Holy Greaves
items.addedLore: Many blacksmiths have tried to craft their products in this armor's image, but none so far have been able to capture the brilliance of these Bovemist-blessed greaves.

items.name: Ignition
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Forged with flaming scales shorn from Ozoth, the fabled Golden Ninja of the Canyon of the Lost hunted his prey relentlessly using this lightweight, yet harder than steel, polearm.

items.name: Infinity
items.addedLore: If you reach for ammunition from your quiver, as long as you have a single arrow, you will find you never run out.

items.name: Influence
items.addedLore: This knife does not belong in your hands... yet somehow it feels right at home.

items.name: Iron Knuckle
items.addedLore: These bulky-looking gauntlets are actually extremely lightweight, being created of a magical elf-blessed iron alloy blend.

items.name: Iron String
items.addedLore: Many said making a bow out of iron would be slow and wasteful, but the weight of the iron arrow can pierce even stone.

items.name: Ivory
items.addedLore: The holy blade of the House of Talor was crafted of pure unicorn horns, and consecrated by a hundred priests. Evil spirits are driven away by its mere presence.

items.name: Jiandan Handwraps
items.addedLore: The cloth wraps produced by the canyon Dojo are just that, merely soft cloth. It is left to the users to apply them skillfully in battle, in whatever way they see fit.

items.name: Katoa's Warmth
items.addedLore: Brilliantly golden as the crops from the humble farm, its mere presence fills stomachs and brings comfort, but only to those who are modest and generous.

items.name: Kaze
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] Gentle spirits of the wind attract themselves to the brilliant jewels slotted into this ring, bringing peace to its wearers and those around them.

items.name: Kelight's Shield
items.addedLore: Used by the Temple of the Legends' strongest guard, the shielded plating is enchanted with a powerful ward to stave off the effects of the corruption.

items.name: Knucklebones
items.addedLore: An old Nemract saying is engraved along the metal. "A single toss of the knucklebones can make or break a gambling man."

items.name: Kratke
items.addedLore: Spurred on by a drunken bet, the great Thanos smith Kratke improved a pair of leggings from a rival that were once thought to be perfection.

items.name: Bronze Basic Bracelet
items.addedLore: This bracelet is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

items.name: Bronze Basic Necklace
items.addedLore: This necklace is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

items.name: Bronze Basic Ring
items.addedLore: This ring is awarded to participants of the Legendary Challenge. Its modular design allows it to be upgraded in a number of different ways.

items.name: Diamond Fiber Necklace
items.addedLore: This ultimate version of a necklack was given to less than a handful adventurers. Once on your neck, you can communicate with the ground below as if you grew roots.

items.name: Diamond Fiber Bracelet
items.addedLore: Desired by many of the countless challengers, this bracelet allows you to sense movements over thousands of meters away. It is decorated with rough yet beautiful jewels.

items.name: Diamond Fusion Bracelet
items.addedLore: This bracelet opens up its wearers spirit, filling it with pure elemental knowledge. The ornaments decorating it are without peer.

items.name: Diamond Fiber Ring
items.addedLore: This masterpiece of a ring utilizes powerful electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Wearing it, you can feel a deep connection to the ground below.

items.name: Diamond Hydro Necklace
items.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said and every word was true. With this necklace equipped, you could hear the ocean whisper.

items.name: Diamond Hydro Bracelet
items.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this bracelet on your arm you could ride a wave with your bare feet.

items.name: Diamond Fusion Necklace
items.addedLore: Unlike any other invention this necklace enhances your power and understanding of the elements by a tenfold. The colorful jewels used are almost dizzling you.

items.name: Diamond Fusion Ring
items.addedLore: This mighty ring is the crown jewel amongst elemental rings. Wearing it, your knowledge is no longer limited to a few elements.

items.name: Diamond Solar Bracelet
items.addedLore: The device forged into this perfected bracelet drains all heat from its surrounding. Though it almost burns, you can feel your power growing

items.name: Diamond Hydro Ring
items.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said, and no word was a lie. With this ring on your finger, you could catch a gnat without looking.

items.name: Diamond Solar Necklace
items.addedLore: The masterpiece of a necklace gathers all heat from its surrounding. It is fed to its wearer to maximize the strength of attacks.

items.name: Diamond Static Bracelet
items.addedLore: The heavy shocks coming from this perfected bracelet would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is the enhancement of power.

items.name: Diamond Solar Ring
items.addedLore: The device forged into this flawless ring draws all heat from its surrounding. Though it almost burns, you can feel your abilites enhance.

items.name: Diamond Static Necklace
items.addedLore: The lethal amount of electricity emmited from this often desired necklace fails to kill you, as its pure energy runs through your veins.

items.name: Diamond Static Ring
items.addedLore: The heavy electrical impulses coming from this ring would be lethal under normal circumstances, but the only thing its wearer senses is pure power. A true masterpiece of engineering.

items.name: Diamond Steam Bracelet
items.addedLore: This steam-powered bracelet is sought by many challengers of the Legendary Challenge. They say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

items.name: Diamond Steam Ring
items.addedLore: Users of this perfect model of Legendary Island's steam-powered ring have reported feeling weightless in combat. The jewel of the ring is a perfectly clear diamond.

items.name: Diamond Steam Necklace
items.addedLore: This necklace is the pinnacle of steam-powered technology. Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from the necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all.

items.name: Gold Fiber Bracelet
items.addedLore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can feel a rhythm with each step...

items.name: Gold Fiber Necklace
items.addedLore: This improved version of a bracelet utilizes rare electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You notice a rhythm with each step...

items.name: Gold Fiber Ring
items.addedLore: This improved ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. You can sense a rhythm with each step...

items.name: Gold Fusion Necklace
items.addedLore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses advanced nano-technology to boost its users elemental abilities. Though powerful, there are still a few flaws to be fixed.

items.name: Gold Fusion Bracelet
items.addedLore: This bracelet, decorated with complex ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. Though powerful, there's still a lot to improve.

items.name: Gold Fusion Ring
items.addedLore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a powerful elemental force in you. Though stronger than the previous model, its true potential stays sealed.

items.name: Gold Hydro Bracelet
items.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

items.name: Gold Hydro Necklace
items.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

items.name: Gold Hydro Ring
items.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant insisted. Indeed, you begin to notice how your senses sharpen. But is that the limit...?

items.name: Gold Solar Bracelet
items.addedLore: The device forged into this improved bracelet seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your arm...

items.name: Gold Solar Necklace
items.addedLore: The device forged into this advanced necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your neck...

items.name: Gold Static Necklace
items.addedLore: The strong shock coming from this improved version of the necklace is a small price for its strength, but it has yet to reach its peak.

items.name: Gold Solar Ring
items.addedLore: The device forged into this advanced ring seems to absorb heat. You can feel a warming sensation all over your hand...

items.name: Gold Steam Bracelet
items.addedLore: This impressive bracelet is in high demand. Those who have obtained it say that they feel as if they're "one with the wind" when wearing it.

items.name: Gold Static Bracelet
items.addedLore: The painful shock coming from this improved version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

items.name: Gold Static Ring
items.addedLore: The strong shock coming from this advanced version of the ring is a small price for its power, but it has yet to reach its peak.

items.name: Gold Steam Necklace
items.addedLore: The jewel hanging from this necklace is said to be weightless. While still very powerful, its full potential has yet to be achieved.

items.name: Gold Steam Ring
items.addedLore: While this model of the Steam Ring is far superior to its predecessor, there still lies the capacity for one more upgrade. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

items.name: Legendary Medallion
items.addedLore: This medallion marks its wearer as a true champion. It is awarded to those who have put an unnecessary amount of time into attempting the Legendary Challenge.

items.name: Silver Fiber Bracelet
items.addedLore: This rough looking bracelet utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

items.name: Silver Fiber Ring
items.addedLore: This crude looking ring utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains a whispering.

items.name: Silver Fiber Necklace
items.addedLore: This crude looking necklace utilizes electromagic to expose its wearer to earth's heartbeat. Though for now, it remains quiet.

items.name: Silver Fusion Bracelet
items.addedLore: This bracelet, decorated with simple ornaments, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

items.name: Silver Fusion Ring
items.addedLore: This ring, covered in colorful artifical gems, seems to awaken a strong elemental affinity in you. With some improvements to its core, it could become even better...

items.name: Silver Fusion Necklace
items.addedLore: This necklace, decorated with bright jewels, uses built-in micro-devices to boost its users elemental abilites. There are many upgrades to be made before it reaches its full potential.

items.name: Silver Hydro Bracelet
items.addedLore: You'll fight strong like the tide, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

items.name: Silver Solar Bracelet
items.addedLore: The device forged into this simple bracelet seems to gather heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

items.name: Silver Hydro Necklace
items.addedLore: You'll be wise like the sea, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

items.name: Silver Hydro Ring
items.addedLore: You'll move quick like a river, the merchant said. Although you notice the built-in device's abilities, you feel space for an upgrade.

items.name: Silver Solar Ring
items.addedLore: The device forged into this simple ring seems to absorb heat. You feel a bit lukewarm when wearing it...

items.name: Silver Solar Necklace
items.addedLore: The device forged into this basic necklace seems to gather heat. You can feel a warm sting when holding it.

items.name: Silver Static Bracelet
items.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the simple, mechanical bracelet without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

items.name: Silver Static Necklace
items.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, tech-enhanced necklace without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

items.name: Silver Static Ring
items.addedLore: Though it's hard to touch the plain, mechanical ring without experiencing a little shock, its capabilities intrigue you...

items.name: Silver Steam Bracelet
items.addedLore: Users who have worn this early model of the Steam Bracelet have reported that they have felt "one with the wind" while wearing it.

items.name: Silver Steam Necklace
items.addedLore: Despite the size of the large jewel hanging from this necklace, it doesn't feel heavy at all. However, the necklace's mechanisms seem incomplete.

items.name: Silver Steam Ring
items.addedLore: This prototype model of the Steam Ring increases the user's agility in combat. The jewel of the ring is crystal clear.

items.name: Alka Cometflinger
items.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and raw potential fuse to create an imposing presence, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for complete obliteration.

items.name: Augoeides
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Disco
items.addedLore: Recovered from a corrupted soldier who wore them, it was found dancing instead of attacking those around it. Even after it was killed, it jostled and jerked around like a dancing puppet.

items.name: Hunger
items.addedLore: Forgotten long ago, these boots curse the wearer with an endless hunger.

items.name: Nepta Floodbringer
items.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and immense wisdom meld to create a commanding aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for dominion over all.

items.name: Masochist
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Sitis
items.addedLore: Wielding it for too long will leave one a dessicated husk, as this dull blade slowly absorbs all liquids around it.

items.name: Starburst
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: The Eviscerator
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Relic
items.addedLore: Despite being proven unrelated, this enigmatic bow was the lynchpin to beginning the great search for the Relics.

items.name: Thrunda Ripsaw
items.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and consuming fury combine to create a deadly aura, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for utter cataclysm.

items.name: Zephra Shredder
items.addedLore: Combined power of inscribed Uth runes and sheer rage intertwine to create a fearsome sight, as this weapon is merely a spiritual extension of the user's desire for total destruction.

items.name: Legendary Smasher
items.addedLore: Many have tried to duplicate the properties of this spear, but very few have succeeded in enchanting a spearhead with explosive magic that does not cause the spear itself to explode.

items.name: Lemon Legs
items.addedLore: Due to an unfortunate accident where he choked on a lemon, an unremarkable mercenary became a laughing stock. He later managed to shed the title, as he left no one alive who remembered the name.

items.name: Leo
items.addedLore: This thick skinned jacket, imbued with the courage of a thousand lion hearts, will grant the user massive protection from all who target them.

items.name: Libra
items.addedLore: Before the invention of magical weight detectors, there was a giant pair of public scales in Cinfras. Instead of being thrown away, they were reforged to be a formidable piece of armour.

items.name: Little Inferno
items.addedLore: It is cold to the touch until worn. Once donned, it engulfs the wearer in excruciatingly hot flames, but never shall the wearer burn; only their enemies will feel the pain of the fire.

items.name: Locrian
items.addedLore: Skien's trust in others was shattered permanently by the wielder of this dagger, who fell to the corruption and attacked his legion during a great corrupted siege.

items.name: Luminis
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Lunar Spine
items.addedLore: From the Nether Gate, a shard of cosmic stone was ejected. Its purity was defiled, and the first man to wield it went mad, raving about the fall of the cosmos' beauty.

items.name: Alkatraz
items.addedLore: Soul-locking magic is one outlawed by Gavellian governments, only used by the most insidious and cruel of mages. One such enchantment looms dormant in this mundane-looking maul. Continued usage of the weapon threatens to release it upon the wielder, permanently binding them to the weapon.

items.name: Apocalypse
items.addedLore: Forged from the tooth of the fallen one, this spear was bargained to a human for his soul, not knowing that the weapon itself would claim all life.

items.name: Az
items.addedLore: Mysterious runes, held by inexplicable ancient guardians, were once moulded together for study purposes. The experiment went awry, as the the runic words Nii, Az, and Ek were combined in a reaction that resulted in the collapse of a civilization.

items.name: Archangel
items.addedLore: The unwieldy, yet imposing stature of this massive sickle strikes awe into those who view it. Those who have the will to wield it, however, seem to garner respect from all those around them, as though they had become a god.

items.name: Boreal
items.addedLore: The last known crafts of Theorick before his fall in battle were pieces of armour crafted out of pure ice, all of which have melted save for these shimmering boots. Wearing them will cause one's very biology to change, becoming enriched and nurtured by sheer cold, while heat will only bring death.

items.name: Crusade Sabatons
items.addedLore: One of the very few physically-powerful artifacts of the Villagers, these boots were used in the initial crusades against the Green-skins, to overpower the Orcs via raw physical might. Though effective, they have not seen use in a long time.

items.name: Cataclysm
items.addedLore: Despite the existence of the Nether Portal, few believe that it is possible to open such rifts with sheer force alone. None believe that a tool with enough power to accomplish such a monumental feat could exist. And yet...

items.name: Discoverer
items.addedLore: Wealth and riches...but at what cost?

items.name: Fatal
items.addedLore: A mage by the name of Lero claims to have harnessed the sheer power of lightning using a magical staff, however, the weapon is very unreliable in a pinch.

items.name: Freedom
items.addedLore: Freedom of soul, mind, and body are forced upon all those that this bow's arrows impact, and freedom of caring from the atrocities that such a dangerous weapon can inflict is given to all those that hold it.

items.name: Gaia
items.addedLore: The Dernel tribes revere various nature deities, each in their own unique fashions. One of the most notable was that of a lost tribe, who fashioned this blossoming stave as tribute to their deity of the earth itself.

items.name: Galleon
items.addedLore: Forged with the raw powers of both the earth and the sea, these boots were initially an attempt at creating a method of foot-travel over the seas. Despite the spectacular failure of that application, they remain a formidable and reliable set of armor.

items.name: Grandmother
items.addedLore: The very first crossbow in existence was claimed to be utterly indestructible, but it is only true to a fault. The item cannot be broken, but solely because all damage to it is instead reflected onto the user. As its age is uncountably ancient, wielders will find themselves rapidly aging and withering away with even a mere touch.

items.name: Grimtrap
items.addedLore: Found at the site of the Caritat Mansion, this simple-looking glove is bathed in dark presence. It wracks those who wear it with pain, and instills the belief that the only way to end the pain is not to remove the item, but to inflict that same torment upon all others.

items.name: Guardian
items.addedLore: A vow of protection hangs over this spear, now inhabited by the spirit of a legendary heroine. Even simply a glimpse of the burning blade will instill a feeling of protection and security, and that feeling will hold true if one is brave enough to wield it.

items.name: Idol
items.addedLore: Intricate carvings and images, almost like that of a totem pole, cover the shaft of this marvelous trident, dredged up from the Seavale Reef. Foreign magics heighten the senses of its user in battle, but also instills a longing for the ocean. Many have succumbed to this urge and drowned themselves.

items.name: Hero
items.addedLore: Enigmatically, this weapon will only show itself to those who believe themselves to be worth nothing, or to be weak. While utilizing this weapon will greatly strengthen one's resolve, it will disappear when it is no longer needed, going to the next wielder.

items.name: Ignis
items.addedLore: This bow, used by the dwarves to land the final blow in the slaughter of Garaheth is extremely powerful. Special, fire resistant gloves must be worn at all times to prevent burns to the user.

items.name: Inferno
items.addedLore: The Dogun God Garaheth was actually an immense fire demon occupying the bowels of Molten Heights. Although unwise, the Dwarves forged a demonic dagger using his tooth in celebration of his slaughter.

items.name: Lament
items.addedLore: When the lost city of Sarnfic sunk beneath the depths, nothing but the bubbles of screams and this single wand surfaced. When used, you can still hear the towns lament.

items.name: Nirvana
items.addedLore: Spiritual enlightenment is a goal that many monks hope to one day grasp the barest glimpse of, often thought to be a goal that must be worked towards over a lifetime. Holding this polished, translucent blade will instantly induce that lofty state until it is let go.

items.name: Monster
items.addedLore: This wand merges with the user on touch, bringing about horrific changes to them. Elongated nails, sharp teeth and the ability to breathe fire are trademarks of the beast.

items.name: Pure
items.addedLore: Carved directly from the mysterious rock that hit Gavel 50 years ago, this pure white wand glows with cosmic energy unknown.

items.name: Slayer
items.addedLore: Many artifacts are found to incite rage in the wearer, and wizards old and new alike conjecture as to the purpose of them. Very few increase the latent abilities of the wearers to ensure havoc, and none to such a degree as these boots.

items.name: Spring
items.addedLore: Arrows fired by this bow are pure ice, but when they hit the enemy, burst into magical water, flash-freezing all that it touches. The frost burns will never heal.

items.name: Thrundacrack
items.addedLore: The raw aspect of thunder, though claimed to be harnessed by a mage in a wand, has only been truly tamed by this mighty blade. Combined electric and life-draining magic intertwine and bring forth the truest, most frightening power of all Thunder.

items.name: Warchief
items.addedLore: Sheer strength exudes from these Orcish relics, simple sandals ill-fitting to humans or Villagers. Enchanted with power and rage rather than magic, the strength that is provided when they are worn is unparalleled.

items.name: Stratiformis
items.addedLore: The Elves managed to harness the power of air itself, forming a bow made entirely of air currents, allowing the user to move swift like the wind, but vulnerable to attacks.

items.name: Warp
items.addedLore: The notorious and erratic magical inventor Gawrick once attempted to make teleportation scrolls obsolete, by creating items which would allow the user to phase into an ethereal state to move unhindered. He did not account for the physical ramifications of this process, however.

items.name: Weathered
items.addedLore: A relic of the past in Time Valley was weathered down to a dagger by the sheer power of the wind. When used in battle, mysterious intertwined wind and time magic give it no physical presence.

items.name: Maelstrom
items.addedLore: Lost by master sailor Carvel in a massive storm, it was carried all the way out to the city of Selchar, where it was found spewing seafoam and lightning bolts.

items.name: Maltic's Old Spear
items.addedLore: This short spear was the first weapon to be produced by the villagers for sale. They are old, but strong.

items.name: Martyr
items.addedLore: A recently married man went off to war wearing this wedding ring. Though he perished in battle, his courage and determination empowers all who wear it.

items.name: Marvel
items.addedLore: The stellar quality of the coral jewels set into the ring comes from a magical purification process, involving a decade-long soak in mystical Gylia water.

items.name: Matryoshka Shell
items.addedLore: The armor worn by the enigmatic Matryoshka Idol. It appears to have a nearly uncountably high number of inlets and sockets set inside.

items.name: Meanderthal
items.addedLore: These boots were retrieved from a frozen man, uncovered on an expedition to Mt. Wynn. It is believed that the man had been wandering the world before his death.

items.name: Master
items.addedLore: Although not truly magical by any means, the sheer craftsmanship of this ornate broach makes its wearers feel skillful.

items.name: Memento
items.addedLore: All those who wear these enchanted boots deposit a single fond memory into them. They are forgotten forever, but wearing them recalls every memory within vividly.

items.name: Mesarock Arch
items.addedLore: The two mesa tribes once were allies until their sacred totems were stolen. Before that time, however, they often shared their talents, and this bow hewn from mesa stone was one such lost craft.

items.name: Millennium
items.addedLore: Cosmic energy permeates this deceptively dull-looking chestplate, having been crafted with stardust from a comet that only passes over Wynn every 1000 years.

items.name: Momentum
items.addedLore: This golden cuff has an odd time dilation effect surrounding it, slowing all movements significantly, but multiplying the force of impact to a significant degree.

items.name: Morrowind
items.addedLore: One of many lost artifacts from the legendary Wind Fortress, the engraving appears to be a cryptic clue to where the Fortress fell. "We shall be found among the dark winds of the morrow."

items.name: Abyssal Amulet
items.addedLore: Used by the Order of the Abyss to aid their summoning rituals, it contains a strange, fiery energy. It has ties with a terrible demon...

items.name: Abysso Galoshes
items.addedLore: Rumored to be crafted from a Dernic stone, these sinister boots radiate extremely powerful dark energy. They have absorbed the power of the raging seas in their time locked in Sarnfic.

items.name: Altum Spatium
items.addedLore: Even looking at this pendant strains your eyes. Should it even exist?

items.name: Blood Moon
items.addedLore: Imbued with the blood of the first werewolf, it was kept in Gelibord as a trophy before being stolen. Wearing it is said to mimic the effects of the lycanthropic curse.

items.name: Bob's Battle Chestplate
items.addedLore: This battered chestplate was once worn by the legendary Wynnic protector, Bob, during the fearsome corrupted sieges before he gave it away to an old friend. An air of melancholy hangs over it.

items.name: Clearsight Spectacles
items.addedLore: Ancient magicks are required to make these brilliant glasses, imbued with charity and selflessness. They allow sight beyond sight, rumoured to allow sight of a brilliant realm.

items.name: Contest Wynner Cap
items.addedLore: I won!

items.name: Mummy's Rag
items.addedLore: The accursed mummy once wore this robe as a great pharaoh of the desert. It has long since rotted, leaving only a cursed shell of its former greatness.

items.name: Olux's Prized Dagger
items.addedLore: This expertly crafted dagger was smithed by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It can chop through even the thickest of the swamp's clay with ease.

items.name: Olux's Prized Bow
items.addedLore: This expertly crafted bow was whittled by a cryptid-researching fanatic. Its frame was cut from the very toughest tree roots.

items.name: Olux's Prized Spear
items.addedLore: This expertly crafted spear was forged by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shines brilliantly in even the weakest sunlight.

items.name: Olux's Prized Wand
items.addedLore: This expertly crafted wand was shaped by a cryptid-researching fanatic. It shimmers with the purest water from the swamp.

items.name: Phoenix Prince's Crown
items.addedLore: The Phoenix Prince is a mythical figure spoken of in Avos legend. His crown cursed him in an endless cycle of death and rebirth.

items.name: Royal Blazing Amulet
items.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It glows with a comforting warmth.

items.name: Royal Cyclone Amulet
items.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It whistles with an invigorating tune.

items.name: Royal Dusty Amulet
items.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It shines with a powerful strength.

items.name: Royal Shocking Amulet
items.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It crackles with a chaotic energy.

items.name: Royal Stormy Amulet
items.addedLore: An exclusive amulet given to the most honored knights of Wynn. It pulsates with a calming aura.

items.name: Seekers Aid
items.addedLore: I found them!

items.name: Sodeta Boots
items.addedLore: These boots were standard issue to members of the prestigious, and now disbanded, Sodeta Guild, and given as a gift to the owners of Delnar Mansion one day.

items.name: Wynnter Fair 2016 Souvenir
items.addedLore: Thank you for participating in the 2016 Wynnter Fair!

items.name: Wynnterfest 2016 Souvenir
items.addedLore: Thank you for participating in Wynnterfest 2016!

items.name: Wynnter Fair 2017 Souvenir
items.addedLore: Thank you for participating in the 2017 Wynnter Fair!

items.name: Yellow Content Cap of Fame
items.addedLore: I helped!

items.name: Necklace of a Thousand Storms
items.addedLore: Sealed away by the Avos of the old days to prevent it from falling into the wrong hands, this necklace was enchanted to strengthen its wearers spiritual link to nature itself.

items.name: Nemract's Rage
items.addedLore: A year-long monsoon soaked this Nemract-made bow so much, that it has harnessed the very essence of water.

items.name: Nemract's Ruin
items.addedLore: This chestplate was originally created as a memorial ornament to the lost lives of Ancient Nemract before being reforged into a powerful piece of armor for Nemract's guard.

items.name: Neolithic
items.addedLore: This ancient stone-hewn helmet is blended with the bones of an extinct animal of some kind. It is harder than dragon's hide.

items.name: Nether's Scar
items.addedLore: Forged directly from the bloody red stone mined from the Nether, they were locked away for fear of inciting insanity in those who wore them.

items.name: Ohms' Wish
items.addedLore: "If anyone finds this, leave it at my Gale's gravesite. I promised her a memento, too." This inscription is extremely weathered.

items.name: Old Keeper's Ring
items.addedLore: Found on the corpse of the oldest shopkeeper of the Gavel province, the engraved text reads 'GREED'.

items.name: Omnitread Boots
items.addedLore: Plated with enchanted metals, these magic-warding boots allow faster travel over nearly any solid surface.

items.name: Opulenity
items.addedLore: Made of an uncommonly used fabric called denim, these fashionable leggings exude style and elegance. Surely wearing them would bring you luck?

items.name: Oyster
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Pandemonium
items.addedLore: Power, but at what cost?

items.name: Passus Lux
items.addedLore: A brilliant relic supposedly originating from the Realm of Light, the creators of these strangely shaped boots are completely unknown.

items.name: Pelier
items.addedLore: Occasional whisperings can be heard by the wearers of this stone mask, reforged from a phylactery of souls. Although not dangerous, staring into the eyes of the mask can bring fear of one's soul being trapped within.

items.name: Petrichor
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Phoenix Wing
items.addedLore: The magically rejuvenating properties of phoenix ash were imbued into this grand stave in its creator's bid to gain immortality.

items.name: Planet Healer
items.addedLore: The jewels in this necklace naturally draw darkness and corruption into its wearer, purifying the land around them at the cost of their own life.

items.name: Pisces
items.addedLore: The oddly uncomfortable helmet was hand sculpted from a mystic clay found only in the depths of Molten Heights. Not much is known about the substance.

items.name: Post-Ultima
items.addedLore: These leggings are the last remaining piece of a historical set of armor, created with such power as to be thought impossible long ago.

items.name: Precious
items.addedLore: A strange magic attracts you to this ring. Maybe you shouldn't tell anyone about its existence?

items.name: Prism
items.addedLore: The jewel on this ring is found very rarely deep beneath the Light Forest. It has the power to manipulate light itself.

items.name: Pulsar
items.addedLore: The density of this weapon is almost immeasurable. Despite being light and easy to wield, the spear seems to have its own gravitational pull, slowly dragging enemies closer and making it nearly impossible to put down.

items.name: Prymari
items.addedLore: This staff was expertly crafted from fragile spun glass, and tinted with various magical foci that bend light into its most raw components.

items.name: Proxima
items.addedLore: This spear is bright enough that it can cause blindness if you look directly at it. Its immense power is limited by its weight; the weapon is nearly impossible to lift.

items.name: Puppeteer
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Cerid's Ingenuity
items.addedLore: One of the master tinkerer Cerid's greatest inventions, these odd gear-laced boots clink and chime with the sound of clockworks keeping its powerful magic dynamos constantly running.

items.name: Gale's Sight
items.addedLore: True to their promise, these goggles were left as a memento for Ohms when his lover Gale finally died. Light as air, Gale's carefree nature lends itself to those who don them.

items.name: Ensa's Faith
items.addedLore: The scholar-priest Ensa created this pendant as a personal prayer while his home was under siege. It is rumored to hold the key to enlightenment, but it is unknown as to how.

items.name: Ohms' Rage
items.addedLore: These ancient, spark-coursing greaves are all that remains of the great thunder mage Ohms' favorite golem familiar after a dark force turned it against its masters.

items.name: Remikas' Authority
items.addedLore: This plain-looking silver bracer is one of the last surviving heirlooms of the first Gavelian king, to be passed down to his heirs. The shimmering metal is said to contain Remikas' soul within it.

items.name: Rycar's Elation
items.addedLore: Created from the lip of a wine bottle and dropped in the mystic waters of Lake Gylia, this glass ring seems to follow Rycar's drunken escapades wherever she wanders.

items.name: Tisaun's Valor
items.addedLore: Tisaun, a warrior tasked to fend off a corrupted siege alone, could find only a thin shirt and rusted spear to use before the attack. He defeated all 1000 enemies without taking a scratch, and his bravery infused his gear with that same strength.

items.name: Ragni's Mail
items.addedLore: One of the few remaining standard issue mails that were used against the first hordes to emerge from the infamous portal over 1000 years ago.

items.name: Rarity
items.addedLore: Being one of the absolute rarest treasures in the world, it seems to have a mind of its own, only showing itself when a stroke of luck is had.

items.name: Reaper of Soul
items.addedLore: A grave digger uncovered this blade from the resting place of a notorious pirate that pillaged the islands of the ocean for four decades.

items.name: Red Candle
items.addedLore: The flickering flame atop this simple wand is a marvel of magic. It always burns at a comfortable heat, cannot scorch skin even if touched, and never can be snuffed out under any circumstance.

items.name: Remikas' Righteousness
items.addedLore: Despite this mace never seeing use by Remikas, it was seen as a symbol of the might of his rule over Gavel. Its true abilities in battle have never been seen.

items.name: Reticence
items.addedLore: Many old mages had to perform lengthy incantations to make potent even their simplest spells. A mage cursed to be mute, however, brought upon a revolution to spellcasting through this simple wand.

items.name: Return to Ether
items.addedLore: This enigmatic weapon can suddenly blink out of reality with no warning only to appear exactly where it was left later. Artificers have determined that almost the entire bow, by all known laws of nature and magic, should not exist.

items.name: Rewind
items.addedLore: Time moves in strange ways around this translucent blade, speeding and slowing, starting and stopping, with no observable reasoning or pattern.

items.name: Rikter
items.addedLore: Named for an ancient Wynnic word for "Earthquake", this mighty battle hammer causes the very bones of struck enemies to rattle and heave as though the earth itself was splitting under their feet.

items.name: Chipped Glitz
items.addedLore: There are little chips and cracks all over this... was someone trying to break it down for gold?

items.name: Broken Sandust
items.addedLore: The silver looks rather tarnished...does he expect you to believe that "gem" isn't just a cheap glass bauble?

items.name: Enhanced Coalwalkers
items.addedLore: Even ignoring the numerous scorches all over, these boots hardly look any better.

items.name: Enhanced Copper Plate
items.addedLore: The merchant insists that the wear and oxidation on the armor "is a feature."

items.name: Enhanced Pickpockets
items.addedLore: Aside from the added plating, they look more or less intact. Somehow, that doesn't surprise you.

items.name: Enhanced DuskShield
items.addedLore: They look extremely bulky and uncomfortable...do they have a right to call it "enhanced"?

items.name: Cracked Stonehall
items.addedLore: It looks like someone tried and failed to improve it. The re-smithing job was obviously rushed...

items.name: Upgraded Dark Needle
items.addedLore: The magic in this wand seems much weaker than normal...and there's a rather rude message written on the handle.

items.name: Upgraded Archpriest
items.addedLore: It seems stronger at first glance, but upon closer inspection the blade is rather...soft?

items.name: Upgraded Radiance
items.addedLore: The craftsmanship on this bow is rather poor. The paint on the "crystals" is chipping...

items.name: Upgraded Steel Buster
items.addedLore: It is significantly heavier than usual...you can't tell if that is good or not, in this case.

items.name: Upgraded Whisper
items.addedLore: The blade seems sharper than normal, but it also seems rather brittle. The smithing was obviously a hack-job...

items.name: Used Wolf Paw
items.addedLore: It looks more like a dog paw to you, but you don't feel like risking your life arguing with the merchant.

items.name: Diving Boots I
items.addedLore: Just a test item.

items.name: Diving Boots III
items.addedLore: Just a test item.

items.name: Diving Boots II
items.addedLore: Just a test item.

items.name: Sagittarius
items.addedLore: The hide of the centaur is extraordinarily magical in the right hands. It is told to allow the user to gain the swiftness of the horse, but also leaves them vulnerable to hard hitting attacks.

items.name: Sage
items.addedLore: Discipline and experience is channeled into these wands for 10 years in the Bantisu monastery of the canyon, in the hope that they will pass on its teachings to less experienced users.

items.name: Sawdust
items.addedLore: Once cursed by a druid who had his grove chopped away by a greedy Villager, it was then purified and mass-produced for sale as armor, to the druid's utter disappointment.

items.name: Scorpio
items.addedLore: The carapace of the common Maexi pet fire scarabs, while alone, only cause minor burns to the touch. However, when woven together, they produce a variety of cumulative effects.

items.name: Scorpion
items.addedLore: This dagger has no blade. Instead, it is layered with the stingers of the Black Shadow Scorpion, which has the ability to vanish entirely from its prey.

items.name: Scythe
items.addedLore: A psychopath claiming herself to be Death incarnate used this dark-bladed scythe on a killing spree that lasted over a year. It reaped hundreds of lives, including her own.

items.name: Seven-League Boots
items.addedLore: Bending the fabric of reality to allow the wearer to take massive strides, these boots are rumored to contain rogue djinni to power them.

items.name: Shatterglass
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] This small, rough-crafted pendant is the only known magic artifact of the Orcs. It incites destructive tendencies within the wearer.

items.name: Shawl of Gaea
items.addedLore: Despite being thin enough to blow away in the wind, this mineral-blended shawl holds the force of a supervolcano within its soft fabric.

items.name: Shinespark
items.addedLore: There have been many attempts to create a reliable power system in Llevigar, and this plasma-charged helmet was reforged from a notable prototype.

items.name: Sigil of Existence
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: Skin Piercer
items.addedLore: The average bow can boast a range of skills, but unlike this one, not every bow can penetrate through any organic skin, including dragon hide.

items.name: Soundwave
items.addedLore: This bow's thick string fails to shoot arrows effectively, but instead produces low frequency sound waves that erupt from the source in all directions. The sound can implode the eardrums of an enemy with a single strum.

items.name: Spectre
items.addedLore: The dark spectres of the decayed forests have created an insidious helmet to drain the spirit of those who wear it, and become servants to their dark whims. Many have fallen to its allure.

items.name: Spiritshock
items.addedLore: Potentially one of the most dangerous weapons in existence. A precise enough shot can destroy the soul of those it hits.

items.name: Squall's Breath
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\]

items.name: StabSand
items.addedLore: The art of endurance fighting is a skill lost to time. However, a thief that to this day has not been caught, imbued this dagger with the very same ability.

items.name: Stalagmites
items.addedLore: Although these boots are crafted from corrupted stone, they do not exhibit any corruptive effects on their wearers. Speculation abounds as to the reason.

items.name: Steamjet Walkers
items.addedLore: A rogue inventor stole the plans for a steam jet booster from Corkus and reverse engineered them onto a set of boots. While effective, they are dangerous, prone to catastrophic failure.

items.name: Stellar
items.addedLore: Elementally attuned gemstones are melded together to form the singular marvel found on this pendant. Despite the violent smithing process, the jewel is utterly flawless.

items.name: Taurus
items.addedLore: The hide of the Touroto, an almost invincible Bull-like creature, is said to be pierced only by the horn of the Tauroto itself, making it extremely valuable.

items.name: Tenuto
items.addedLore: This strange pendant has been known to dilate time around the wearer, slowing their movements while greatly augmenting their power.

items.name: The Berserk
items.addedLore: Forged from unbreakable obsidian eras ago, this heavy hammer has crushed many foes with a single swing.

items.name: The Berserker's Helm
items.addedLore: Worn by a terrible berserker during his fanatical rampage through the land, his rage permeates this horned blackiron helmet.

items.name: The Divide
items.addedLore: Once having held unstoppable amounts of magic, being forced to fuse into one form locked away all but the smallest sliver of their power.

items.name: The Exile
items.addedLore: This indestructible dagger was found floating in the magma of the Molten Heights, with a lament from its exiled smith carved onto the hilt.

items.name: The Forgery
items.addedLore: While only a mockery of the original product, this line of helmets became wildly popular before legal disputes and safety concerns halted production.

items.name: Third Eye
items.addedLore: The Bantisu monks have developed this enigmatic sigil in their years of meditation and study. It blesses the wearer with luck and powerful psionic ability.

items.name: Thunderbolt
items.addedLore: This bow has no string. Instead, a thin lightning-like thread is strung upon it. It is said to be limited only by the speed of the user.

items.name: Tidebinder
items.addedLore: This mysterious, half-liquid trident apparently holds the secret magics to control the ocean's ebb and flow. It is incapable of touching solid ground.

items.name: Toaster
items.addedLore: \[Community Event Winner\] This peculiar weapon was once wielded by the firey warrior Igbar, who used it to great effect in nether-endurance competitions.

items.name: Tisaun's Proof
items.addedLore: The wear upon this broken old battle spear does not affect its ability in battle. The souls of a thousand fallen warriors resound within it.

items.name: Torrential Tide
items.addedLore: The tides of the ocean, once bound, became useful magic power sources. They were once utilized for weapons, but to harness the unstable force of the raging sea was considered too dangerous.

items.name: Vaward
items.addedLore: A once-great hero left behind these sturdy, reliable greaves, trusting those after her to be able to use their power to protect others, should they don them. Her courage fuels their wearers.

items.name: Venison
items.addedLore: This ancient Elven sacrifical mask contains only a sliver of its previous magic, yet the blessing of the Elven god Entia still greatly empowers those who don it.

items.name: Ventus Tail
items.addedLore: Fashioned from the cut tails of the now extinct Venti, these nearly immaterial boots are light as air and crackle with lightning.

items.name: Virgo
items.addedLore: These common leather boots were once owned by a barbarian with no magical prowess, who, instead of enchanting it, added a hundred boab spikes to each boot to punish enemies.

items.name: Waves Raiser
items.addedLore: The mystery of the oceans appearance has eluded scholars for centuries. It is believed that many years ago, warlocks used wands like this one in an attempt to submerge the world.

items.name: Winter's Essence
items.addedLore: These pure, snow-white leggings are rumored to have been crafted by the legendary ice mage Theorick. The people of Nesaak view them as cursed, seeking to destroy them in a bid to stop the endless winter surrounding them.

items.name: Zero
items.addedLore: The unstable power within this bow is capable of great destruction, but seems to zero out at the most crucial moments in battle. Only the most skillful archers can wield this weapon with confidence.

items.name: default
items.addedLore: This is a rad weapon yo. Let's make the lore longer so we can test how long it can go. Hi Jumla!
